# Partrunner Design System

Source of truth for all visual decisions in this project.

## Colors (use Tailwind tokens, never hardcode hex)

| Token | Hex | Use |
|---|---|---|
| `partrunner-yellow` | #FFD840 | Primary: headers, CTAs, badges |
| `partrunner-yellow-dark` | #FED330 | Hover states |
| `partrunner-yellow-accent` | #F29F05 | Text accents, icons |
| `partrunner-yellow-light` | #FFF9E5 | Callout backgrounds |
| `partrunner-black` | #14142B | Primary text, headings |
| `partrunner-gray-dark` | #4E4B66 | Body text |
| `partrunner-gray-light` | #D9DBE9 | Borders, dividers |
| `partrunner-bg-main` | #F5F7FB | Page background |
| `partrunner-bg-card` | #FFFFFF | Cards, modals |

## Typography — Inter only

- Headlines: `font-bold` (700)
- Body: `font-normal` (400)
- Labels: `text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider`
- NEVER use Bebas Neue, Barlow, or monospace for user-facing text

## Components (use CSS classes from index.css)

- `.btn-primary` — yellow CTA with glow shadow
- `.btn-secondary` — gray neutral
- `.btn-ghost` — transparent
- `.card` — white, rounded-2xl, shadow-card, border
- `.input-base` — white, border-2, yellow focus ring

## Logo assets in public/images/

- On yellow bg → `logo-full-black.png`
- On dark bg → `logo-full-white.png`
- Favicon → `icon-color.png`

## Editorial images (AI-generated)

- Brand color in prompts: #FFD840 (not #FDD238 or #FFC107)
- AI models cannot render text — headlines are metadata for overlay
- prompt_compiled should request "clean negative space for text overlay"
- **Logo identity:** The real logo PNG is sent as a reference image to Gemini alongside prompt_compiled
- prompt_compiled MUST include: "The Partrunner logo shown in the reference image must appear IDENTICALLY reproduced"
- Logo variant is selected by Claude in the editorial JSON and mapped to the correct PNG via LOGO_VARIANT_MAP in server.ts
- NEVER describe the logo textually for the image model — always rely on the reference image
